[{"body": "The Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index (JCI) remained in the green zone, closing at 7,778.91, with a slight increase from 7,734.90 at 9 am WIB, driven by gains in other indices such as LQ45, IDX30, IDX80, and IDXESGL. Several stocks, including PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia TBK and PT Indofood CBP Sukses Makmur TBK, saw strong upward movements, while others, like PT Chandra Asri Pacific TBK and PT Bank Mandiri TBK, were corrected.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50982/afternoon-session-jci-improvement", "sub_sector": ["banks", "basic-materials"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "LQ45", "IDX30", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BBRI.JK", "TPIA.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-24T14:49:21", "title": "Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index Remains in Green Zone Despite Early Dip"}, {"body": "PT Bank DBS Indonesia has launched its investment account service, offering competitive interest rates of 1% per annum and free administration fees, with a target of recording 1 million new stock exchange investors within the next 5 years. The bank aims to achieve double-digit growth in its asset under management, having already reached a double-digit growth rate year-to-date, and plans to introduce a US-dollar-based RDN service by 2025.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50981/bank-dbs-indonesia-mirae-asset-launch-multi-currency-rdn", "sub_sector": ["alternative-energy", "apparel-luxury-goods", "automobiles-components"], "tags": ["Interest Rates", "IDX", "Fintech", "Market Trends", "Bonds", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["AALI.JK", "ABMM.JK", "ACES.JK", "ACST.JK", "ADHI.JK", "ADMF.JK", "ADMR.JK", "ADRO.JK", "AG